                        Proof 9. That God, requiring obedience of children to Parents, promiſed a reward; ſaying, Honour thy father and mother, that thy dayes may be long in the land, which the Lord ſhall give thee; which ſurely was not ſpoken to one, but to all the ſons of men,

for with God there is no exception of perſons, but as a juſt and pious father, he gives to every one according to his deſerts,
terram autem dedit filiis hominum.

And of the whole madcap, fraternity;
for they will be ſworn brothers, fraterimi aut fratres in malo, we may well ſay.
Peſtis, qua gelidum, Boreae,
violentius axem;
Nulla vel infecit nulla
vel inficiet.
A greater plague, to this
our Northern clime;
Never yet came nor can
in after time.
